Plotting Summary

Plotting Systems

Base

The plotting system that ships with R

x<-1:100
y<-x+rnorm(100)

plot()

plot(x,y)

hist()

hist(x)

boxplot()

boxplot(x)

Lattice

code for Trellis graphics

library(lattice)
library(datasets)

xyplot()

xyplot(Ozone ~ Wind, data = airquality, pch = 12) # options from base, see ?par and ?points

xyplot(Ozone ~ Wind | as.factor(Month), data = airquality, layout = c(5,1))

bwplot()

bwplot(Ozone ~ Wind, data= airquality)

ggplot2

Based on the Grammar of Graphics

library(ggplot2)

qplot()

qplot() is a wrapper for 

qplot(displ, hwy, data = mpg)

qplot(displ, hwy, data = mpg, facets = drv ~ .) + geom_smooth(method="lm")

qplot(y=hwy, data = mpg, color=drv)

qplot(drv, hwy, data = mpg, geom = "boxplot", color=manufacturer)

qplot(hwy, data = mpg, fill = drv, geom = "density")

geom_point()

Adding point geometry

g <- ggplot(mpg, aes(cyl, cty))
g + geom_point()
